King William I was king from 1165 to 1214.

The study included H1/6/ documents and H1/1000/59, 71, 74, 76, a total of 405 documents. 390 of these were charters, 8 charter/brieves, 4 notifications, and 3 settlements.

The <a href="http://db.poms.ac.uk/sna/all/6/" target="_blank">SNA visualization</a> included 405 documents from his reign, to which there were 394 witnesses with 14,694 ties between them.

